@Node "intro" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

DrawerBall is a directory tool, allowing you listing drawers and files and process functions on them.
DrawerBall is started from @{"Workbench" link "wb"} or @{"Shell" link "use"} with one option required; directory.
By startup is the directory listed. At top is amount of drawer(s), file(s) and total bytes filesizes (64bits) given.

@EndNode
@Node "Distribution" 
@{b}Distribution and copyright@{ub}

DrawerBall is freeware.

@EndNode
@Node "Tip" 
@{b}Tip@{ub}

*recommended is SFS as filesystem, because it supports long filenames more seen nowadays. SFSDoctor 1.5 in MorphOS 2 distribution
 helps me once to recover 240 files by a crash. Do not anoying validating whole harddisk so now and then as FFS does.
 HDConfig in MorphOS 2.5 is bugfixed.

*Efika users: a tip is to set the max. width for a lister, say, 475, go to pulldown-submenu "Project/Settings/Lister view".
 Also, the DrawerBallBMBGRA version use graphic cards memory, leaving more normal memory free, handy for low on memory situations
 as for the Efika. Be sure that Ambient is a 24/32bit BGRA screen. Tough, these version is not faster in scrollingm, do
 not know why: BltBitMapRastPort() instead of WritePixelArray() is used, internaly, BGRA cgx bitmap is allocated and rendered in.

*you can copy text from any other programm in the rename string gadget: click left mouse-button and move with the mouse over the
 text you wanna copy, release then the left mouse-button, and press the right special "Amiga" (Windows) key with key "C". Go to
 DrawerBall and press special right "Amiga" (Windows) key with key "V" in the rename window string gadget. Other handy text
 controls: press key "Shift" and "left arrow" key to go to the beginning of the textline, "Shift" and "right arrow" key to the
 end of the textline. "Shift"+"Del" delete all text right of the cursor.

@EndNode
