@Node "use" "How to use DrawerBall"

DrawerBall is started from Shell.

@{u}@{b}Shell usage:@{uu}@{ub}

The following commandline options are supported:
------------------------------------------------

TEMPLATE:

	DrawerBall,NAME

NAME=directory or device to show at startup, use no quotes, name with spaces are readed OK.


Shell (CLI) Examples:
---------------------

@{fg shine}-1-@{fg text}

@{fg fill}DrawerBall DH0:@{fg text}

List the device DH0: in a window lister

@{fg shine}-2-@{fg text}

@{fg fill}DrawerBall Work:MorphOS/Butter fly@{fg text}

List the directory "Work:MorphOS/Butter fly" in a window lister

@EndNode
@Node "wb" "Workbench"
@{b}Starting from Workbench@{ub}

DrawerBall can be started from Workbench from the icon, SYS: as directory is loaded by default.
You can select files and or drawers in the window, and choose a function from the @{"pull-down menus" link "pulldownmenus"}
to process on them after each other. Additionaly, you can create own defined @{"user menus" link "pulldownmenus_project_settings_usermenus"}.

@EndNode
@Node "Require" "Requirements"

Minimal Requirements:

DrawerBall: MorphOS
DrawerBallBMBGRA: MorphOS and 24bit BGRA screen

@EndNode
@Node "bugs" "Known bugs"

-1 Pulldown-menu "File/Information" don't work with RAM: T:, nothing happens.
-2 "Restart" pressed in "Buffers sizes settings" window, the destination directory must be defined again.
   (while showing RAM: holds the old destination directory, tough)
-3 Slow media as USB connected drives, memorysticks and CD-ROM gives the follow troubles:
   Hangs the lister by refreshing, because the transfer is not finished yet, clicking arround at gadgets and so on
   helps mostly. Advice is to copy/delete file(s), not whole drawer(s), so it's not confused.
   Problems with USB: copy drawers USB memorystick endlessly copy same file, can't get out of the subdir.
   copy bootpartition from my Pegasos II to USB memorystick goes OK.
   copy single files from USB memorystick goes OK.
   Update 0.9m+MOS 2.4 copy drawers on CD-ROM to other media, only one file in each (sub)dir is copied. Copy drawers from
   USB memorystick to other media: gives copycheck requester asking overwrite file (these copied before), choose
   "Skip all" and all files in each (sub)dir is copied correctly. Seems for me the unbuffered Read() Write() causes the
   troubles. Copy delay helps not. The special DrawerBall version which use asyncio library helps not either.

@EndNode
@Node "tech" "Technical"

*DrawerBall uses an off-screen ARGB regtangle allocated once by startup.

*DrawerBallBMBGRA version use graphic cards memory, each time a lister is openend, a cgx BGRA bitmap is
 allocated. It this fails, DrawerBallBMBGRA quits leaving a message: to little memory for bitmap.

*DrawerBall.guide resides in the same directory DrawerBall is, to let pull-down menu "Project/Help" working,
 this is checked, nothing happens when it's not present.

*no cgx_wpa my own programmed wpa replacement uses direct cgx bitmap writing.

@EndNode
@Node "Compilation" "Compilation of DrawerBall"
    
DrawerBall is assembled with vasm & vlink from the vbcc C package.

Freeware software used:

MCalc -programmers suitable calculator.
Snoopium -shows much system calls, good for anylizing programs. (MOS)
Scout -shows much information about the Pegasos, also screens/windows (MOS)
AutoDocReader -to read autodocs that bescribes the Amiga/MorphOS functions. (MOS)
PPC680x0 -translate 68K sources to PPC, without it, this program was not possible.
CygnusEd Professional V4.23 PPC -famous texteditor. (MOS)

My Amiga configuration:

 Amiga1200T 68060 59Mhz, 603e 200Mhz, ROM 3.1, OS3.9 BB2, RAM 128Mb, SCSI HD 8Gb,
 IDE DVD 16x40x, SCSI CD-R 6x4x, PARALLELZIP 100Mb, FlickerFixer/Scandoubler,
 Mediator Voodoo5 graphics with picasso96

 Processor board is BlizzardPPC with SCSI2 (Overclocked the 68060 to 59Mhz)

My (a new) Pegasos II configuration:

 Pegasos II G4 1Ghz, MorphOS 1.4.5, 2.5, 1GbRAM, PHILIPS DVDR16LS Dual DVD with LIGHTSCRIBE,
 WD 120G HD, Belinea 107065 monitor, PixelView Pro TV-Radio, UMAX speakers,
 Radeon 9250, Elbox USB2 card (it's almost empty, they show an older model on their website www.elbox.com).

I'am a proudly Efika owner too.

@EndNode
