@Node "pulldownmenus_project_open" "Pull-down menu Project/Open"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Open@{ub}

Opens a requester to choose a directory or volume to list in the window.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_parent" "Pull-down menu Project/Parent"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Parent@{ub}

List parent directory, is ghosted when this is not possible.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_refresh" "Pull-down menu Project/Refresh"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Refresh@{ub}

Reload directory.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_setdest" "Pull-down menu Project/Set destination"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Set destination@{ub}

Set destination directory used by @{"copy" link "pulldownmenus_file_copy"} and @{"user menus" link "pulldownmenus_project_settings_usermenus"}.
RAM: is default destination directory.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_listerc" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Lister colors"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Lister colors@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the window lister gradient colors, file color
and drawer color.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_windowc" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Windows colors"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Windows colors@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the windows gradient colors.
These colors are used for opened windows as for example the "Rename" window.
Note, that on resize the window the position and width is then used for all opened windows.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_buffersizes" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Buffer sizes"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Buffer sizes@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the follow buffers in megabytes:
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Copy:@{fg text}@{bg back}      the buffer used for copy, if set to 10, means 10Mb is used, a 20Mb file is then copied in 2 parts.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Lister:@{fg text}@{bg back}    buffer holding filenames, do not use large values here
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Dir stack:@{fg text}@{bg back} do not use large values here
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Dir depth:@{fg text}@{bg back} buffer holding fileinfoblocks, do not use large values here, actualy, 1 is enough for 984 subdirectories tree deep
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Bitmap:@{fg text}@{bg back}    buffer for the off-screen ARGB regtangle used for display, great values are used here,
            my download directory needs 54Mb ! Not available for DrawerBallBMBGRA.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_dateformats" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Date formats"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Date formats@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the Date and time formats.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_usermenus" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/User menus"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/User menus@{ub}

An "User menus settings" window is opened where you can change the usermenus or add them if not present.
Click on an already created usermenu button and an usermenu titled window opens,
here you can change the usermenu items or add them if not present.
Click on an already created usermenu items button and a "Usermenuitem function settings" window
opens. In the first two strings, you can change the usermenu name and menuitem name.
Remember, an usermenu is not created if it has no menuitem(s).

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} define the commandline programm executing

 an usermenu execute requires that are at least one file or drawer is selected.
 supported options are case sensetive and always begins with percentage charracter: 

 %P path source drawer lister with slash, example -> DH1:Graphics/mypictures/
 %p path source drawer lister without slash, example -> DH1:Graphics/mypictures
 %s source (selected) file or drawer
 %D @{"destination drawer" link "pulldownmenus_project_setdest"} with slash, example -> Downloads:mypictures/
 %d @{"destination drawer" link "pulldownmenus_project_setdest"} without slash, example -> Downloads:mypictures
 %i input window, usage: %i<MYWINDOWTEXT>%i where <MYWINDOWTEXT> is the text that appears in the input window
 %h comment text, which contains often the http:// string if file was downloaded from the internet
 %c currentdir @{"destination directory" link "pulldownmenus_project_setdest"}, can be placed anywhere in the commandline once.
 %C currentdir own defined directory, can be placed anywhere in the commandline once, usage: %C<MYCURRENTDIR>%C
 %n next function commandline behind this option.
 %r refresh lister.
 %l lister refreshed with new defined drawer, enable "Start always" too. Do not use other options together with this option %l

 @{i}notes about the options:@{ui}

 to read selected file(s) and/or drawer(s) that contain spaces in their name(s), use quotionmarks arround the option(s):
 "%s" only not when "All atonce" is enabled, then %s
 "%P%s" source path+filename
 "%D%s" destination path+filename

 if pressed "Cancel" in the input window, the executing for this selection is aborted, goes on with next then.

 option %c or %C only once used on a commandline, do not use both the same time in a commandline

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Output window:@{fg text}@{bg back} output properties, at end is the enable button.

 own output window enabled: once opened and all outputs from all selections goes to if "Multitasking" is not enabled.
 is "Multitasking" enabled, then for each selection is an output window opened !
 output window is closed if an usermenu executing happens again, last one is closed by quiting DrawerBall,
 this is not by "Multitasking" enabled, then it must wait when the executed command is finished.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Stack in Kb:@{fg text}@{bg back} stack is measured in Kbytes, in the Ambient Information window, it's in bytes.
 Thus first divide with 1024 to be DrawerBall compatible.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Priority:@{fg text}@{bg back} give priority, default zero.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Multitasking:@{fg text}@{bg back} enable multitasking, default disabled.
 some programms multitasks always, even if DrawerBall "Multitasking" button is not enabled.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}All atonce:@{fg text}@{bg back} if "All atonce" is enabled, option %s holds all selections and the commandline is executed once.
 keep in mind that the commandline is limited in lenght, so you can not choose to much selected files/drawers then !

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Start always:@{fg text}@{bg back} execute usermenu once regardles of selected file(s) and or drawer(s).
 for launching a single programm needed. function do not deselect bar(s) when finished
 
@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_listerview" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Lister view"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Lister view@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the lister view appearances.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Extra space filename:@{fg text}@{bg back} By default is 1, set zero if you want the most compact width window, beware then
                       it can happen that by non-proportional fonts the longest filename directly to the
                       largest filesize is, without space.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Stay selected:@{fg text}@{bg back}        Selected file(s) and or drawer(s) stay(s) selected after process a function.
                       Default not enabled.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Status and comment:@{fg text}@{bg back}   By default protection and comment are listed.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Max. left,top,width,height:@{fg text}@{bg back} bounderies for window can be modified, zero means screen dimensions used,
                       checked min. width is 64, height 256, is top=0 then lister becomes under screenbar.
                       be sure that the filled in left and width do not exceed the screenwidth, as well for
                       top and height not greater then screenheight.
                       DrawerBall takes care for the window borders, tough.
                       when left is 512 and width is 512 the lister comes at the half of a screenwidth of 1024 (1024/2=512)
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}No cgx_wpa:@{fg text}@{bg back}           Disable CGX/WritePixelArray() for scrolling only, used is then my own programmed
                       custom writepixelarray routine. Use only if Ambient is in 24bit screen ! Not available
                       for DrawerBallBMBGRA.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_settings_copyrename" "Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Copy, rename"
@{b}Pull-down submenu Project/Setings/Copy, rename@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the copy, rename settings.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Copy comment:@{fg text}@{bg back}  by default enabled, faster copy when disabled.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Unprotects:@{fg text}@{bg back}    overwrite protected files by copy.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Rename string:@{fg text}@{bg back} toggle "name", then the rename window stringinput holds the name (default), "Stays" first name
                and previous input(s) stays, handy for multiple renames with different versions of the same name.
                "Empty", then rename window stringinput is clear, handy to copy&paste text(s) in.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Copy delay 1/50s@{fg text}@{bg back} Add delay in 1/50 seconds after file is entirely copied, default 75=1.5 sec. PFS-II filesystem
                needs it.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_savesettings" "Pull-down menu Project/Save settings"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Save settings@{ub}

Save settings, user menus settings stores in a separate file.
Sort mode is also saved.
Position and width opened windows are saved too.
Stored in the directory DrawerBall is in.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_help" "Pull-down menu Project/Help"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Help@{ub}

Launch the amigaguide documentation

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_about" "Pull-down menu Project/About"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/About@{ub}

Programm version and assembling date information.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_project_quit" "Pull-down menu Project/Quit"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Quit@{ub}

Quit programm quickly.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_openwith" "Pull-down menu File/Open with"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Open with@{ub}

A requester appears, choose a programm to execute with the selected file(s) and or drawer(s).
Selections are processed after each other.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_copy" "Pull-down menu File/Copy"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Copy@{ub}

Copies selected file(s) and or drawer(s) to the @{"destination directory" link "pulldownmenus_project_setdest"}.
If a file will becoming overwrited, a window appears for asking skipping or replacing this file.
Also you can choose "Skip all", "Replace all" and "Abort" copy. "Version" button allows you to compare
the version of the overwritten file,
@{"copy buffer" link "pulldownmenus_project_settings_buffersizes"} is used to load the file and search the version. Is the file bigger in size, increase
then the copy buffer because the last part of the file isn't searched in.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_delete" "Pull-down menu File/Delete"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Delete@{ub}

Requester appears asking if you are sure deleting file(s) and or drawer(s).
Pressing "OK" button deletes the selected file(s) and/or drawer(s).

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_newdrawer" "Pull-down menu File/New drawer"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/New drawer@{ub}

Create new drawer, also drawer icon can be created. If drawer already exists, an icon can be created too for this drawer.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_rename" "Pull-down menu File/Rename"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Rename@{ub}

Rename selected file(s) and/or drawer(s). Press close gadget to abort.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_info" "Pull-down menu File/Information"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Information@{ub}

Gives the Information window for the selected file(s) and or drawer(s).
It appears 10 times if 10 selected files were chosen, it's an own task.
In the information window, you can modify comment and protection bits, version for files can be shown
as well as total filesize in drawers.
Refresh lister by yourself, because DrawerBall can not determine if information requester returns
and save or cancel button was pressed.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_version" "Pull-down menu File/Version"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Version@{ub}

Gives the version for the selected file(s), libraries.
@{"copy buffer" link "pulldownmenus_project_settings_buffersizes"} is used to load the file and search the version. Is the file bigger in size, increase
then the copy buffer because the last part of the file isn't searched in.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_search" "Pull-down menu File/Search"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Search@{ub}

Search in this window a name, the matched file(s) and/or drawer(s) becomes selected. Already selected
are ignored. Disable the "Ignore case" button for case sensetive searching.
Enable the "Thru files" button for searching into files, in (sub)dirs is not searched thru files.
@{"copy buffer" link "pulldownmenus_project_settings_buffersizes"} is used to search thru the file. Is the file bigger in size, increase
then the copy buffer because the last part of the file isn't searched in.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_execute" "Pull-down menu File/Execute"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Execute@{ub}

Execute the selected file(s) and/or drawer(s) with the commandline arguments typed in the execute window.
"file is not executable" requester appears if file can not be executed.
Press close gadget to abort.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_selall" "Pull-down menu File/Select all"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Select all@{ub}

Select all file(s) and/or drawer(s).

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_file_invall" "Pull-down menu File/Invert all"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Invert all@{ub}

Toggles file(s) and/or drawer(s) selections inverted.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_sort_nosort" "Pull-down menu Sort/No sort"
@{b}Pull-down menu Sort/No sort@{ub}

Listed the drawer(s) and file(s) as it appears on disk.
Handy in some cases.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_sort_namecase" "Pull-down menu Sort/Name case"
@{b}Pull-down menu Sort/Name case@{ub}

Listed the drawer(s) and or file(s) alphabeticaly, uppercases at top.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_sort_date" "Pull-down menu Sort/Date"
@{b}Pull-down menu Sort/Name Date@{ub}

Listed the drawer(s) and or file(s) at newest date.
Most recent date at top.

@EndNode
@Node "pulldownmenus_history" "Pull-down menu History"
@{b}Pull-down menu History@{ub}

Listed are the visited directories, oldest at top. At startup are the volumes/assigns listed.

@EndNode
